b"[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](sbe48442.htm)  [Next](sbe48444.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n60\\. And on account of injunction.\n\nThe above conclusion is further confirmed by the fact of injunction, i.e.\nthereby that clauses such as 'he is to meditate on the Udgitha' enjoin the\nmeditation as standing to the Udgitha in the relation of a subordinate member.\nInjunctions of this kind differ from injunctions such as 'he is to bring water\nin the godohana vessel for him who desires cattle'; for the latter state a\nspecial qualification on the part of him who performs the action, while the\nformer do not, and hence cannot claim independence.\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: 61. On account of rectification](sbe48444.htm)\n\n"